                <p>Other members of the immediate <term ref="#t819" type="subject">family</term> and relatives. List for each the Name, Age,
                    Relationship, Last known address, Former permanent address, Occupation and Employment, if known. (Continue on reverse side of page
                    as necessary.)</p>
                <p>no relatives.</p>
                <p>Face Sheet prepared by: <persName ref="#ehri_et_roninson_victor" type="ehri">Victor Roninson</persName></p>
                <p>Team:</p>
                <p>567</p>
                <p>Date: <date when="1946-04-24">24 April 1946</date>.</p>
                <p>Information obtained from:</p>
                <p><persName ref="#ehri_et_holz_sonja" type="ehri">Holz, Sonja</persName></p>
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-YV5082493_02.jpg" n="2"/>
                <p>First displacement</p>
                <p><date when="1942-06">June 1942</date> – brought with <term ref="#t822" type="subject">family</term> into <term ref="#t545"
                        type="subject">Ghetto</term>.</p>
                <p>Separation from <term ref="#t819" type="subject">Family</term></p>
                <p><term ref="#t822" type="subject">Mother</term> and younger <term ref="#t822" type="subject">brother</term> (about six yrs. old)
                        <term ref="#t745" type="subject">killed</term> in <term ref="#t545" type="subject">ghetto</term>.</p>
                <p>Older <term ref="#t822" type="subject">brother</term> (about eighteen yrs of age) <term ref="#t532" type="subject">shot</term> in
                        <term ref="#t545" type="subject">ghetto</term>, because he did not wear the <term ref="#t338" type="subject">yellow
                        star</term>.</p>
                <p>Her <term ref="#t822" type="subject">father</term> has been <term ref="#t518" type="subject">taken away</term> and she never saw
                    him again. (All this happened in <date when="1942-06">June 1942</date> in the <placeName ref="#l292" type="ghetto">ghetto of
                        Wolomin</placeName>).</p>
                <p>Moves and changes</p>
                <p>Summer <date when="1943">1943</date> - Taken by <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term> to
                        <placeName ref="#riga" type="ehri">Riga</placeName> (<placeName ref="#republic-of-latvia" type="ehri">Latvia</placeName>);</p>
                <p>Worked there for a farmer, living in the <placeName ref="#l788" type="camp">camp of Kaiserwald</placeName> (<placeName
                        ref="#republic-of-latvia" type="ehri">Latvia</placeName>), submitted to all atrocities of <orgName ref="#g429" type="ehri"
                        >German SS-men and women</orgName>.</p>
                <p>Then brought to <placeName ref="#strassenhof" type="ehri">Strassenhof</placeName> (<placeName ref="#republic-of-latvia" type="ehri"
                        >Latvia</placeName>), where she worked in an ammunition <term ref="#t929" type="subject">Factory</term>.</p>
                <p>Summer <date when="1944">1944</date> - <placeName ref="#l857" type="camp">Stutthof</placeName> (<term ref="#t496" type="subject">C.
                        C</term>. near <placeName ref="#gdansk" type="ehri">Danzig</placeName>).</p>
                <p>Winter <date when="1944">1944-1945</date>-<date when="1945">1945</date> - walking to <placeName ref="#kalkow" type="ehri"
                        >Kalkau</placeName>, as <term ref="#t623" type="subject">evacuated</term> from <placeName ref="#l857" type="camp"
                        >Stutthof</placeName>.</p>
                <p><date when="1945-03">March 1945</date> - <term ref="#t573" type="subject">liberated</term> by <orgName ref="#g004583" type="ehri"
                        >Russian troops</orgName>.</p>
                <p>Sick with <term ref="#t493" type="subject">Typhus</term>, stays at the house of a farmer, being taken care of by a <term
                        ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_russians" type="subject">Russian</term>
                    <term ref="#t287" type="subject">physician</term>. Then goes to <placeName ref="#bialystok" type="ehri">Byalistok</placeName>
                        (<placeName ref="#republic-of-poland" type="ehri">Poland</placeName>) <term ref="#t227" type="subject">seeking family</term>,
                    without success.</p>
                <p><date when="1945-06-12">12 June 1945</date> - <placeName ref="#bielsk" type="ehri">Bielsk</placeName> (<placeName
                        ref="#republic-of-poland" type="ehri">Poland</placeName>), <term ref="#t824" type="subject">Children</term>'s home of the
                        <orgName ref="#ehri_et_the_jewish_central_committee_at_warsaw" type="ehri">Jewish Central Committee at Warsaw</orgName>.</p>
                <p><date when="1945-08">August 1945</date> - <placeName ref="#slonsk" type="ehri">Zabrza (Slonsk)</placeName>, <placeName
                        ref="#republic-of-poland" type="ehri">Poland</placeName>: <placeName ref="#state-of-israel" type="ehri">Kibutz Tel
                        Iczhak</placeName>.</p>
                <p><date when="1945-11">November 1945</date> - <term ref="#t278" type="subject">D.P. Camp</term>
                    <placeName ref="#foehrenwald" type="ehri">Föhrenwald</placeName>, <placeName ref="#wolfratshausen" type="ehri"
                        >Wolfratshausen</placeName>.</p>
                <p>Language</p>
                <p>Yiddish, Polish, Hebrew.</p>
                <p>Documents</p>
                <p>D.P. 1 – Card (see reg. No.).</p>
                <p><term ref="#t1134" type="subject">School</term> record</p>
                <p>Finished the fifth grade grammar <term ref="#t1134" type="subject">school</term>.</p>
                <p>She is now a dressmaker apprentice in this <term ref="#t278" type="subject">camp</term>.</p>
                <p>She also attends grammar <term ref="#t1134" type="subject">school</term> courses in the <term ref="#t278" type="subject"
                        >camp</term>.</p>
                <p>Information re <term ref="#t822" type="subject">family.</term></p>
                <p>Her <term ref="#t822" type="subject">father</term> was a salesman in a <term ref="#t836" type="subject">clothing</term> store at
                        <placeName ref="#vilnius" type="ehri">Vilna</placeName>.</p>
                <p>Her <term ref="#t822" type="subject">mother</term> was a dressmaker on her own.</p>
                <p>They were three <term ref="#t824" type="subject">children</term> at home.</p>
            </div>
